  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advocacy and reconciliation in communities afected by socio-political and environmental conflicts</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to contribute to reconciliation process in Colombia through the strengthening of democracy, including advocacy. It will be implemented at different -but interlinked- levels to achieve the proposed objectives. At local level the strengthening of the advocacy and public opinion capacities of civil society organizations and ecclesiastical jurisdictions will foster a process of advocacy in the territories most affected responding to their local problems. At national level SNPS will influence and generate public opinion regarding the different topics of interest of local territorial organizations, as well as generating campaigns and communicative strategies for the positioning of different topics aimed at peace and reconciliation. Finally, at international level with the accompaniment of the Caritas Working Group for Colombia (GTC) and the different advocacy platforms, political pressure exercises can be carried out as well as education and awareness about issues relevant to the country.</narrative>
  </description>
